properties.documentation: A <font color="#c93500">Platform </font>is an entity that <font color="#c93500">hosts </font>other entities, particularly <font color="#c93500">Sensors</font>, <font color="#c93500">Actuators</font>, <font color="#c93500">Samplers</font>, and other <font color="#c93500">Platforms</font>.

The thing whose property is being estimated or calculated in the course of an <font color="#c93500">Observation </font>to arrive at a <font color="#c93500">Result</font>, or whose property is being manipulated by an <font color="#c93500">Actuator</font>, or which is being sampled or transformed in an act of <font color="#c93500">Sampling</font>.
Feature which is intended to be representative of a <font color="#c93500">FeatureOfInterest </font>on which <font color="#c93500">Observations</font> may be made.
An actuatable quality (property, characteristic) of a <font color="#c93500">FeatureOfInterest</font>.
An observable quality (property, characteristic) of a <font color="#c93500">FeatureOfInterest</font>.

Act of carrying out an (Observation) <font color="#c93500">Procedure </font>to estimate or calculate a value of a property of a <font color="#c93500">FeatureOfInterest</font>. Links to a <font color="#c93500">Sensor </font>to describe what made the <font color="#c93500">Observation </font>and how; links to an <font color="#c93500">ObservableProperty </font>to describe what the result is an estimate of, and to a <font color="#c93500">FeatureOfInterest </font>to detail what that property was associated with.
An Actuation carries out an (Actuation) Procedure to change the state of the world using an Actuator.

A workflow, protocol, plan, algorithm, or computational method specifying how to make an <font color="#c93500">Observation</font>, create a <font color="#c93500">Sample</font>, or make a change to the state of the world (via an <font color="#c93500">Actuator</font>). A <font color="#c93500">Procedure</font> is reusable, and might be involved in many <font color="#c93500">Observations</font>, <font color="#c93500">Samplings</font>, or <font color="#c93500">Actuations</font>. It explains the steps to be carried out to arrive at reproducible <font color="#c93500">Results</font>.
An act of <font color="#c93500">Sampling </font>carries out a (Sampling) <font color="#c93500">Procedure </font>to create or transform one or more <font color="#c93500">Samples</font>.
XML Schema: dateTime values may be viewed as objects with integer-valued year, month, day, hour and minute properties, a decimal-valued second property, and a boolean timezoned property.

The <font color="#c93500">Result </font>of an <font color="#c93500">Observation</font>, <font color="#c93500">Actuation</font>, or act of <font color="#c93500">Sampling</font>. To store an observation's simple result value one can use the <font color="#c93500">hasSimpleResult </font>property.
OWL: A temporal interval or instant.
A device that is used by, or implements, an (Actuation) <font color="#c93500">Procedure </font>that changes the state of the world.
A device that is used by, or implements, a (Sampling) <font color="#c93500">Procedure </font>to create or transform one or more samples.

Device agent (including humans), or software (simulation) involved in, or implementing, a <font color="#c93500">Procedure</font>. <font color="#c93500">Sensors </font>respond to a <font color="#c93500">Stimulus</font>, e.g., a change in the environment, or <font color="#c93500">Input </font>data composed from the <font color="#c93500">Results </font>of prior <font color="#c93500">Observations</font>, and generate a <font color="#c93500">Result</font>. <font color="#c93500">Sensors </font>can be mounted on <font color="#c93500">Platforms</font>.
